cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a deep learning method based on Graph Convolutional Networks (GCN) for fusing multiple modalities of brain images in relationship prediction for Parkinson's Disease. This involves analyzing neuroimages, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of deep learning also suggests artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves analyzing and predicting disease progression, which falls under neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (cs.CL) in terms of interpreting the results and presenting them in a clear and concise manner.
